value.0: The wall has collapsed inwards here, opening up into a shaft leading down into the earth, pitch-black and foul smelling. Crude hand-holds have been carved into the walls of this tunnel, and sounds of movement echo up from below.
A thick wooden door, with a small barred window. There are small scratches around the keyhole - the hallmark of many a hurried entrance and exit.

A string of poorly cured fox skins hang from the pole. Matted fur and tangles of flesh line the skins, while the edges are jagged and torn, clearly the result of a careless and ill-made knife. Blood still drips from one, pooling below into a small puddle that stains another bundle of hide.

The utensils lining the shelves of this cupboard are rusted brittle, metal worn down by time and misuse. A number of bottles are tucked away inside, and a close inspection would reveal their contents - a mix of blood, bone and bile, a foul alchemist's private stash.

A pile of dirt and fecal matter is pressed into the corner of the room - the crude toilet of its goblin inhabitants. Bodily fluids and waste ooze from the mass and the entire thing stinks tremendously.
Spilt wine stains the ground beneath these barrels, the result of crude gashes torn through the wood by grubby hands and knives.
